Key Match Events: Rohit Sharma scored 92 off 41 balls, marking the fastest ever against Australia.
Travis Head scored 76 but was eventually dismissed.
Glenn Maxwell hit a switch-hit six off Ravindra Jadeja.
Jasprit Bumrah removed Travis Head with a googly.
Post-Match Reflections: Mitch Marsh described the loss as 'disappointing'.
Rohit Sharma felt satisfied with India's performance and backed Kuldeep Yadav's role.
Australia's hopes of progressing to the semi-finals depend on Afghanistan's results against Bangladesh.
Miscellaneous Highlights: David Warner was dismissed early in the chase.
Australia's net run rate was affected by their loss.
Axar Patel and Hardik Pandya bowled well towards the end of the game.
